# GitHub Deploy — Arcane Dice Co.

**Target repository:** `https://github.com/HRBlackwood/Arcane-Dice.git`

## One-time setup (if not already done)

Add the target repo as a remote named `arcane`:

```bash
git remote add arcane https://github.com/HRBlackwood/Arcane-Dice.git
```

Verify both remotes are present:

```bash
git remote -v
# origin   https://github.com/khan-pog/dice-website.git
# arcane   https://github.com/HRBlackwood/Arcane-Dice.git
```

## Deploy workflow

When the user asks to "deploy", "push to GitHub", or "commit and push", always follow this sequence:

```bash
# 1. Stage all changes
git add .

# 2. Commit with a descriptive message
git commit -m "your message here"

# 3. Push to HRBlackwood/Arcane-Dice
git push arcane main
```

If the branch is not `main`, replace `main` with the current branch name (`git branch --show-current`).

## Commit message conventions

- `feat:` — new feature or product added
- `fix:` — bug fix
- `update:` — content or copy changes (products, location, text)
- `style:` — visual/CSS changes only
- `chore:` — config, deps, gitignore changes

## Never do

- Never force push to `main` unless the user explicitly requests it
- Never commit `.env.local`, `.clerk/`, or any file matching `.env*.local`
- Never push the `.next/` build folder (it is gitignored)
